            "          {# INFO_COMMENT  Microsoft Outlook does not properly support the CSS max-width property, especially not combined with multiple columns displayed side-by-side; which is why the so-called ghost tables are needed (=fallback HTML tables, only displayed for Outlook Clients, to yield the same layout / behavior as the one coded with max-width for other clients)  #}\r",
            "\r",
            "            <!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]>\r",
            "            <table role=\"presentation\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"{{styles.mail_max_width}}\">\r",
